name: 16S rRNA (uracil1498-N3)-methyltransferase
reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + uracil1498 in 16S rRNA = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + N3-methyluracil1498 in 16S rRNA
comment: The enzyme specifically methylates uracil1498 at N3 in 16S rRNA.

references.title: Identification and characterization of RsmE, the founding member of a new RNA base methyltransferase family.
Substrate specificity and properties of the Escherichia coli 16S rRNA methyltransferase, RsmE.
